{"title_page": "Daniel Beer", "text_new": "'''Daniel Beer''' (born 1973) is Reader in Modern European history at [[Royal Holloway]], University of London. His book, ''The House of the Dead'', won the 2017 Cundill History Prize and was shortlisted for the [[Wolfson History Prize]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pure.royalholloway.ac.uk/portal/en/persons/daniel-beer(9e09fd00-5339-4fc4-b258-412c507d57c4).html|title=Dr Daniel Beer - Research - Royal Holloway, University of London|website=Pure.royalholloway.ac.uk|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/29/house-of-dead-siberian-exile-under-tsars-daniel-beer-review|title=The House of the Dead by Daniel Beer review \u2013 was Siberia hell on earth?|first=Donald|last=Rayfield|date=29 September 2016|accessdate=30 October 2017|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.russianartandculture.com/interview-daniel-beer-author-of-the-house-of-the-dead-siberian-exile-under-the-tsars/|title=INTERVIEW: Daniel Beer, author of The House of the Dead: Siberian Exile Under the Tsars - Russian Art + Culture|date=29 July 2016|website=Russianartandculture.com|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.penguin.co.uk/authors/daniel-beer/71219/|title=Daniel Beer|website=Penguin.co.uk|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* ''Renovating Russia: the Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880-1930.'' [[Cornell University Press]], 2008.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/renovatingrussia00beer_0|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880\u20131930|first=Daniel|last=Beer|date=12 June 2008|publisher=Cornell University Press|accessdate=30 October 2017|via=Cornell University Press|isbn=9780801446276|url-access=registration}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity,1880\u20131930. By Daniel Beer|first=Frances|last=Nethercott|date=1 September 2012|journal=Cultural and Social History|volume=9|issue=3|pages=469\u2013470|doi=10.2752/147800412X13347542916783}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880-1930 (review)|first=Marina|last=Mogilner|date=31 July 2010|journal=Kritika: Explorations in Russian and Eurasian History|volume=11|issue=3|pages=661\u2013672|doi=10.1353/kri.0.0179}}</ref> {{ISBN|978-0801446276}}\n* ''The House of the Dead: Siberian Exile Under the Tsars''. Allen Lane, 2016. {{ISBN|978-1846145377}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kOJQfx4EWcM|title=History at Royal Holloway - Daniel Beer|website=Youtube.com|date=16 June 2015|accessdate=30 October 2017}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_h-0ffglEuk|title=History at Royal Holloway: Meet the staff - Dr Daniel Beer|date=15 April 2013|website=Youtube.com|accessdate=30 October 2017}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.historytoday.com/author/daniel-beer|title=Daniel Beer - History Today|website=Historytoday.com|accessdate=30 October 2017}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beer, Daniel}}\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:Academics of Royal Holloway, University of London]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Historians of Russia]]\n\n\n{{England-historian-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Daniel Beer''' (born 1973) is Reader in Modern European history at [[Royal Holloway]], University of London. His book, ''The House of the Dead'', won the 2017 Cundill History Prize and was shortlisted for the [[Wolfson History Prize]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pure.royalholloway.ac.uk/portal/en/persons/daniel-beer(9e09fd00-5339-4fc4-b258-412c507d57c4).html|title=Dr Daniel Beer - Research - Royal Holloway, University of London|website=Pure.royalholloway.ac.uk|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/29/house-of-dead-siberian-exile-under-tsars-daniel-beer-review|title=The House of the Dead by Daniel Beer review \u2013 was Siberia hell on earth?|first=Donald|last=Rayfield|date=29 September 2016|accessdate=30 October 2017|website=Theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.russianartandculture.com/interview-daniel-beer-author-of-the-house-of-the-dead-siberian-exile-under-the-tsars/|title=INTERVIEW: Daniel Beer, author of The House of the Dead: Siberian Exile Under the Tsars - Russian Art + Culture|date=29 July 2016|website=Russianartandculture.com|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.penguin.co.uk/authors/daniel-beer/71219/|title=Daniel Beer|website=Penguin.co.uk|accessdate=30 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Selected publications==\n* ''Renovating Russia: the Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880-1930.'' [[Cornell University Press]], 2008.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/renovatingrussia00beer_0|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880\u20131930|first=Daniel|last=Beer|date=12 June 2008|publisher=Cornell University Press|accessdate=30 October 2017|via=Cornell University Press|isbn=9780801446276|url-access=registration}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity,1880\u20131930. By Daniel Beer|first=Frances|last=Nethercott|date=1 September 2012|journal=Cultural and Social History|volume=9|issue=3|pages=469\u2013470|doi=10.2752/147800412X13347542916783}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Renovating Russia: The Human Sciences and the Fate of Liberal Modernity, 1880-1930 (review)|first=Marina|last=Mogilner|date=31 July 2010|journal=Kritika: Explorations in Russian and Eurasian History|volume=11|issue=3|pages=661\u2013672|doi=10.1353/kri.0.0179}}</ref> {{ISBN|978-0801446276}}\n* ''The House of the Dead: Siberian Exile Under the Tsars''. Allen Lane, 2016. {{ISBN|978-1846145377}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links=